Array.prototype.forEach = function (callback) { if (callback && typeof callback === 'function') { for (var i = 0; i < this.length; i++) { callback(this[i], i, this); } }
};

5.body:
Probably the most common way to use forEach: let arr = [1,2,3,4,5]; arr.forEach(x => console.log(x)); To pass more arguments: let arr = [1,2,3,4,5]; arr.forEach((x, y) => { console.log(x); console.log(y);
}); Or all three: let arr = [1,2,3,4,5]; arr.forEach((x, y, z) => { console.log(x); console.log(y); console.log(z);
}) Expected Output:
1
0
[1,2,3,4,5]
2
1
[1,2,3,4,5]
3
2
[1,2,3,4,5]
4
3
[1,2,3,4,5]
5
4
[1,2,3,4,5]
